      • AbstractXlScriptProcessor

        public AbstractXlScriptProcessor(java.lang.String baseScript)
        Constructor to set base script which will be accessible from all scripts.

        For instance, if baseScript is "def testMethod(String str) {'hello ' + str}", then any script can call "testMethod('test') // it will return 'hello test'"

        Parameters:
        baseScript -

      • AbstractXlScriptProcessor

        public AbstractXlScriptProcessor(java.lang.Object baseInstance)
        Constructor to set base instance which will be accessible from all scripts.

        For instance, if the class of the instance has "public String testMethod(String str)", then scripts can call testMethod('some value').

        Parameters:
        baseInstance -

      • evaluate

        protected java.lang.Object evaluate(java.lang.String markedScript,
                                    java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> excel,
                                    java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> listElement,
                                    java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> optional)
        Execute markedScript as Groovy script if it is surrounded by backslash. (e.g. `some script here`)

        This method will set following beans to binding context of the script.

        • $excel: excel object given as parameter
        • keys in $excel: For instance, if $excel contains "testList", then it is accessible from script by either "testList" or "$excel.testList"
        • $it: listElement object
        • keys in listElement

        Parameters:
        markedScript -
        excel -
        listElement -
        Returns:
